{"key":"processedPost-10009250","value":{"id":10009250,"first":10003682,"last":10010273,"when":1237591058,"utime":"03/21/09 02:17 AM","content":"Oyster mushrooms are probably the fastest growing mushrooms from inoculation to fruiting.&nbsp; If your friend has oyster spawn, get that instead of spores.&nbsp; It will be much faster.&nbsp; In fact, tell him you want to grow mushrooms in an old shoe, and he'll probably give you what you need.&nbsp; You'll want to boil the shoe in water to kill off the molds, and then fill it up with the sawdust spawn he gives you.&nbsp; Keep it loosely wrapped in plastic until fully colonized, and then set it outside in a shady spot, especially if it's the rainy season, which I'm pretty sure it is in Holland.<br /><br />Here's an art project for ya!<br />RR<br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-26/327075751-Gay_bra_pic.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/07-26/327075751-thumb_Gay_bra_pic.jpg\"></a><br />","title":"Re: Agar art project"}}